PS/2 Mouse Protocol Signal Dumps
================================

This directory contains signal dumps for PS/2 mouse communication.
The PS/2 mouse protocol is a bidirectional synchronous serial protocol
used for mouse input devices.

Protocol Details:
-----------------
- Clock frequency: 10-16.7 kHz (typically ~10 kHz)
- Data format: 11 bits per frame (1 start, 8 data, 1 parity, 1 stop)
- Parity: Odd parity
- Communication: Bidirectional (host can send commands to mouse)
- Voltage levels: 0V (low), 5V (high) with open-collector outputs

Mouse Data Packet Format (Standard 3-byte):
-------------------------------------------
Byte 1: [Y overflow][X overflow][Y sign][X sign][Always 1][Middle][Right][Left]
Byte 2: X movement data (8-bit signed)
Byte 3: Y movement data (8-bit signed)

Extended Protocols:
-------------------
- IntelliMouse: 4-byte packets with scroll wheel data
- IntelliMouse Explorer: 4-byte packets with additional buttons

Files:
------
- ps2_mouse_init.sr: Mouse initialization sequence
- ps2_mouse_movement.sr: Basic mouse movement packets
- ps2_mouse_clicks.sr: Left, right, and middle button clicks
- ps2_mouse_scroll.sr: Scroll wheel data (IntelliMouse protocol)
- ps2_mouse_commands.sr: Host commands to mouse (reset, set resolution, etc.)

Common Mouse Commands:
----------------------
- 0xFF: Reset
- 0xF6: Set Defaults
- 0xF5: Disable Data Reporting
- 0xF4: Enable Data Reporting
- 0xF3: Set Sample Rate
- 0xF2: Get Device ID
- 0xE8: Set Resolution
- 0xE6: Set Scaling 1:1

Mouse Responses:
----------------
- 0xFA: Acknowledge (ACK)
- 0xFE: Resend
- 0xAA: Basic Assurance Test (BAT) completion
- 0x00: Mouse ID (standard mouse)
- 0x03: Mouse ID (IntelliMouse with scroll wheel)
- 0x04: Mouse ID (IntelliMouse Explorer with 5 buttons)

For more information about PS/2 protocol:
https://wiki.osdev.org/PS/2_Mouse
